At YourWay, we are committed to protecting the privacy and security of our users' personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and manage the information gathered through our women's periodic health app.

Information Collection and Use

Personal Information: We may collect personal information such as name, email address, date of birth, and health-related data voluntarily provided by users to improve the app's functionality and offer personalized services.

Health Data: Our app may collect menstrual cycle information, ovulation tracking, pregnancy-related details, and other health-related data entered by users. This data is used solely for providing personalized health insights and improving the user experience.

Information Sharing and Disclosure

Third-Party Services: We may utilize third-party services to enhance our app's functionality. These services might have access to certain user information, but they are obligated to use it solely for the purpose of providing their services to us.

Legal Compliance: We may disclose personal information if required by law or in response to valid legal requests, such as court orders or government regulations.

Data Security

We implement industry-standard security measures to protect the confidentiality and integrity of user information. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and while we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your personal information, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.

User Rights

Access and Control: Users have the right to access, modify, or delete their personal information stored in our app. They can do so by accessing the app settings or contacting us directly.

Opt-Out: Users can choose not to provide certain information or opt-out of specific data collection features within the app.

Children's Privacy

Our app is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that personal information has been collected from a child under 13 without parental consent, we will take steps to delete that information.

Changes to This Privacy Policy

We reserve the right to update or modify this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be effective immediately upon posting the updated Privacy Policy on our app. We encourage users to review this page periodically for any changes.

